content:
A visually distinct dividing line, used to separate content.

## Exports

- **Separator**: A React component that renders a separator element.

## Props

This component accepts all standard `SeparatorPrimitive.Root` props, along with the following:

- `className` (string): Additional CSS classes to apply to the separator.
- `orientation` (enum: `'horizontal'` | `'vertical'`, default: `'horizontal'`): The orientation of the separator.
- `decorative` (boolean, default: `true`): Whether the separator is decorative (screen readers will ignore it).

## Usage

```jsx
import { Separator } from "@/components/ui/separator";

function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div>
      <p>Above Content</p>
      <Separator />
      <p>Below Content</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Vertical Separator

```jsx
import { Separator } from "@/components/ui/separator";

function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center">
      <span>Left Content</span>
      <Separator orientation="vertical" className="mx-4 h-10" />
      <span>Right Content</span>
    </div>
  );
}
```
